org.knime.core.node.workflow

Interface NodeOutPort

  • All Superinterfaces:
    NodeContainerStateObservable, NodePort, NodeStateChangeListener
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NodeContainerOutPort, NodeOutPortWrapper, WorkflowOutPort

    public interface NodeOutPort
extends NodePort, NodeStateChangeListener, NodeContainerStateObservable
    Interface for a node's output port. A variable number of input ports can be connected to it (which are part of the next nodes in the workflow).
    Author:
    Thomas Gabriel, University of Konstanz
    No public API: not to be extended by clients
    This interface is not intended to be extended by clients.
    No public API: not to be implemented by clients
    This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients.

      • getPortSummary

        String getPortSummary()
        Get summary of the underlying port object as provided by PortObject.getSummary(). It's a separate method since calling getPortObject().getSummary() may force the underlying table (if it is a table) to restore its content from disc. Summaries are saved in the workflow file (or the node's corresponding sub directory).
        Returns:
        The port object's summary.

      • isInactive

        boolean isInactive()
        Returns:
        true if the contained spec is not null and instance of InactiveBranchPortObjectSpec

      • getConnectedNodeContainer

        SingleNodeContainer getConnectedNodeContainer()
        The single node container associated with this port. For 'standard' nodes this is just the corresponding node; for metanodes it's the node indirectly connected outside (or inside) or null if not connected.
        Returns:
        the node container as described above, possibly null.
        Since:
        3.2
